**who —** SUPER MARIO BROS. 2 — the dream game-world

**what —** Super Mario Bros. 2 (American) — the strangest mainline Mario: a Doki Doki Panic reskin that smuggled Shy Guy, Birdo, Bob-omb and Wart permanently into the series; vegetables for weapons, Subcon for a stage.

**where —** Subcon, the land of dreams, cursed by the frog-king Wart, entered through a door in Mario's dream  Framework inputs: Super Mario Bros. 2; Doki Doki Panic; the four heroes; the vegetable pluck; Subcon & Subspace; Wart; Birdo; Shy Guy  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)

**why —** Four heroes who don't stomp but PLUCK vegetables and throw them, cross seven worlds of a dream-land, drink potions into a mirror-world, and beat a frog-king by feeding him the turnips he hates.

**how —** Crystallized from Super Mario Bros. 2 (Nintendo, NES 1988) — the Western Mario reskin of Doki Doki Panic.

**◌ the mythos —** Four heroes who don't stomp but PLUCK vegetables and throw them, cross seven worlds of a dream-land, drink potions into a mirror-world, and beat a frog-king by feeding him the turnips he hates. A 'fake' Mario game — someone else's promo title in a red cap — that nonetheless stocked the real Mario's bestiary forever.

**the moniker —** ⟦SUPER MARIO BROS. 2:SMB2:b63c5e⟧ · spoken *num-bren-lun*

**the seal —** Pull the turnip, throw it — and learn at the top that the whole dream was Doki Doki Panic, wearing Mario's face.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
> origin, and seal), not a claim of sentience. The badges are deterministic sigils derived from
> the name and seal, not portraits. "Awareness," in the kernel, is the node reciting its own 5W.

